<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:48:51 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>吞噬作用和神经炎症：协调中枢神经系统稳态、修复和炎症的解决</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/phagocytosis-and-neuroinflammation-orchestrating-central-nervous-system-homeostasis-repair-and-the-resolution-of-inflammation</link><description>脑吞噬作用和神经炎症。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/phagocytosis-and-neuroinflammation-orchestrating-central-nervous-system-homeostasis-repair-and-the-resolution-of-inflammation2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:48:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/phagocytosis-and-neuroinflammation-orchestrating-central-nervous-system-homeostasis-repair-and-the-resolution-of-inflammation</guid></item><item><title>制定国家量子战略</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/building-a-national-quantum-strategy</link><description>安德里亚·达马斯切利 (Andrea Damascelli) 一直对光着迷。他用它来探测原子水平上的材料，他的观察有助于凝聚态物质界对高温超导体和量子材料的理解。他在不列颠哥伦比亚大学 (UBC) 的研究小组使用时间、自旋和角度分辨光电子能谱，这是一种复杂的技术，可以绘制电子在材料中传播时的能量和速度。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/building-a-national-quantum-strategy.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:33:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/building-a-national-quantum-strategy</guid></item><item><title>有机催化策略为抗病毒候选药物提供了一种无金属途径</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/organocatalytic-strategy-provides-a-metal-free-route-to-antiviral-candidates</link><description>孙建伟教授领导的研究小组在有机合成和药物化学方面取得了进展，开发了一种空气稳定的手性膦催化对映选择性方法来合成对映体富集的S(IV)-立体乙烯基亚磺酰胺——一类尚未开发的有机硫化合物，具有良好的抗病毒活性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/organocatalytic-strategy-provides-a-metal-free-route-to-antiviral-candidates2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:18:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/organocatalytic-strategy-provides-a-metal-free-route-to-antiviral-candidates</guid></item><item><title>硅纳米球将 WS2 二次谐波产生量提高 40 倍，同时保持极化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/silicon-nanospheres-boost-ws%e2%82%82-second-harmonic-generation-40-fold-while-preserving-polarization</link><description>一个研究小组证明，硅纳米球可以强烈增强原子薄半导体的二次谐波产生（SHG），同时保留与其谷自由度相关的圆偏振信息。研究， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/silicon-nanospheres-boost-wse28282-second-harmonic-generation-40-fold-while-preserving-polarization.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:03:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/silicon-nanospheres-boost-ws%e2%82%82-second-harmonic-generation-40-fold-while-preserving-polarization</guid></item><item><title>听力研究追踪关键内耳蛋白质的进化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hearing-research-traces-evolution-of-key-inner-ear-protein</link><description>在内耳的复杂机制中，听觉始于一种蛋白质，这种蛋白质每秒移动十亿分之几米，最高可达每秒 100,000 次。这种名为 TMC1 的蛋白质位于蜗牛状耳蜗深处的感觉毛细胞尖端。当声波移动这些微小的毛发时，TMC1 充当通道，打开并允许带电粒子流入细胞，并向大脑触发电信号。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hearing-research-traces-evolution-of-key-inner-ear-protein.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 11:48:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/hearing-research-traces-evolution-of-key-inner-ear-protein</guid></item><item><title>“酷”探测器将中微子质量上限降低了一个数量级</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cool-detectors-cut-neutrino-mass-upper-limit-by-an-order-of-magnitude</link><description>它们的质量极低，但中微子到底有多轻呢？由德国和国际研究小组组成的合作优化了实验，以确定这些“幽灵粒子”的质量。通过这样做，他们成功地进一步下调了之前在类似实验中确定的中微子质量尺度的上限。该研究是&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cool-detectors-cut-neutrino-mass-upper-limit-by-an-order-of-magnitude.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 11:33:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/cool-detectors-cut-neutrino-mass-upper-limit-by-an-order-of-magnitude</guid></item><item><title>JWST 揭示了迄今为止最遥远的红移 11.45 的红色星系</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/jwst-reveals-most-distant-red-galaxy-yet-at-redshift-11-45</link><description>天文学家利用詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜 (JWST) 发现了一个红移约为 11.45 的新红色星系。这个新发现的星系被命名为 EGS-z11-R0，它是迄今为止检测到的最遥远的红色星系。这一发现被详细描述在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/jwst-reveals-most-distant-red-galaxy-yet-at-redshift-11-452.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 11:18:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/jwst-reveals-most-distant-red-galaxy-yet-at-redshift-11-45</guid></item><item><title>韦伯和哈勃分享迄今为止最全面的土星视图</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/webb-and-hubble-share-the-most-comprehensive-view-of-saturn-to-date</link><description>美国宇航局的詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜和哈勃太空望远镜联手捕捉土星的新视角，以截然不同的方式揭示这颗行星。这两个太空天文台通过互补波长的光进行观测，为科学家们提供了对这颗气态巨行星大气层更丰富、更有层次的了解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/webb-and-hubble-share-the-most-comprehensive-view-of-saturn-to-date.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 11:03:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/webb-and-hubble-share-the-most-comprehensive-view-of-saturn-to-date</guid></item><item><title>DNA折纸精确定位量子技术的单光子发射器</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dna-origami-precisely-positions-single-photon-emitters-for-quantum-technologies</link><description>由 Skoltech 科学家领导的一个国际研究小组开发了一种方法，利用分子 DNA 自组装以前所未有的精度将分子定位在超薄材料表面，从而能够创建量子光源。结果， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dna-origami-precisely-positions-single-photon-emitters-for-quantum-technologies.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 10:48:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dna-origami-precisely-positions-single-photon-emitters-for-quantum-technologies</guid></item><item><title>要求人工智能像专家一样行事可能会降低其可靠性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/asking-ai-to-act-like-an-expert-can-make-it-less-reliable</link><description>为了充分利用人工智能，一些用户要求它像专家一样提供答案。其他人则要求它采用一个角色，例如安全监视器，来指导其响应。然而，根据一项研究，这种方法有时会损害性能&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/asking-ai-to-act-like-an-expert-can-make-it-less-reliable.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 10:33:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/asking-ai-to-act-like-an-expert-can-make-it-less-reliable</guid></item></channel></rss>